At least 11 people were killed when a train plowed into a tourist minibus on Friday at a rail crossing in southeast Bangladesh. Three more people were critically injured in the accident in Bangladesh's Chattogram district, some 242 km southeast of the capital Dhaka, at about 1:45 p.m. local time, Kabir Hossain, officer-in-charge of the local Mirsharai police station, told Xinhua.